        String[] quickandsimpleChefMealDescription = {
                "Beware shrimps bearing Greeks? Beware Greeks bearing shrimps? No need to beware of this meal! Instead, luxuriate in yummy pasta, tasty shrimp, and some classic staples of Greek food: salty feta, olives, and fresh oregano. Beware Greeks bearing shrimp? Don't ask us, it's all Greek (and delicious) to us.", "Hatch chiles get their name from the town of the same name in New Mexico, where the soil and growing conditions lead to their subtly spicy flavor. In this dish, the chile is mixed with flavorful ranch seasoning and tangy sour cream, making a sauce that bathes the chicken with pure deliciousness. The meal completes itself with sweet butternut squash with cheese and crunchy pepitas.", "Teriyaki salmon and mushroom fried rice can only come in paper cartons, right? With chopsticks and soy sauce packets, and maybe a few cookies? That's delicious, no doubt, but this is even better: you can make it at home and it only takes about 15 minutes. Take-out is terrific, but this is divine.", "Kefta is a form of Moroccan kebab made with ground beef or lamb and spices. We've left out the skewers, but kept in the flavor, with a fresh salad on the side. (And delicious, creamy tzatziki on top!)", "Is tikki masala British or Indian? The debate rages on, but it doesn't matter here, where all we want to deliver you is flavor and ease. Served with rice and peas on the bottom, and cooling sour cream on top, we leave the debates to the Oxford debate society. (Is that taking a side? Oh dear.)", "Few things are as decadent as creamy honey butter. Sitting atop succulent seared pork, and complemented with cheesy Parmesan broccoli, these flavors will surely elevate you into euphoria.", "The flavors of curry and coconut go together like Batman and Robin. They are flavor super heroes, they each have different, but complementary strengths, and they both wear capes. (That last one may be slightly less than true.) Which one is Batman and which one is Robin? We'll let you decide, since this meal obviously goes together with your future dinner plans.", "Name two better flavors out there than tangy BBQ and ranch... we'll wait. Ok, we won't wait long... these flatbreads highlight both those flavors and then some, with peppery arugula and cheese.", "Caesar salad is one of the best salads out there, but salad for dinner? It's just not enough. You'll be hungry an hour later! You won't be hungry with this meal, that scrumptious garlicky good flavor covering a succulent chicken breast. The crunchy croutons on top raise it from good to perfection.", "Gyros… as the Greek gods on Mt. Olympus intended. (What came first, the gyros or the gods? Question for the ages.) Tender pork, cooked with seasoning and tomatoes, and topped with a bit of light heat with a pepperconi and cucumber crema. These gyros are so good, Zeus would have turned himself into a Home Chef customer for 'em.", "Yo-de-lay, yo-de-lay, yo-de-lay, yo-de-lay eee ooo! That may not be how any of that is spelled, but this sandwich makes us dream we're in the Alps, in a tiny café, with this meaty delicious sandwich and tangy potato salad on the side. We love the mountain life.", "Top your pork chop with nothing but the best: tangy roasted tomato, Asiago, and nutty almonds bring out the best in the meaty chops. Fresh broccoli on the side, with onion and garlic pepper, with sweet balsamic, also give the pork chop an assist. (Not that it needs it; pork chops are tops! Ah, poetry.)", "Yup, what you're looking at right here is a breadless banh mi; all the flavors you love in that classic Vietnamese sandwich, in bowl form. Will the wonders ever cease? Ground pork, flavored with ginger and teriyaki, join pickled cucumbers and carrots in topping fragrant jasmine rice. It's exactly like the sandwich, except, dare we say, even better.", "A chili that takes one pot and comes together in less than 15 minutes? With turkey, corn, cheese, tortilla strips, and sour cream, a.k.a. all the fixings'? Yes, yes, yes, yes, and yes. Is it a miracle? Nope, just Home Chef stovetop meals.", "Easy to make and delightful to eat, these Acapulco-style pork tacos make dinner a festive occasion. Pork strips, seasoned with taco seasoning, fill tortillas along with zesty slaw. Buen provecho!", "The world is full of amazing cuisines to be inspired by, and Vietnamese cuisine is certainly no slouch on that regard. The amazing noodle bowls known as pho delight and tantalize all around the globe. Here, we've got the noodles, and the succulent pork, the pho flavorings… all coming together in your kitchen.", "Need a quick and good pasta bowl to get your week going? Look no further… (no, don't open a new tab…we said look no further!)… than this meal. Meaty sausage, three cheeses, and zesty roasted red peppers all mix with penne in under fifteen minutes. Go ahead, put it in your basket. (No, don't go to Facebook… no, don't click on that link!)", "Dill and seafood go together like two peas in the pod (there are no peas in this recipe), like peanut butter and jelly (not included in your box), or sour cream and onion… which we have right here, being stirred into creamy mashed potatoes. You know what else goes together? You and this dinner.", "This meal has many amazing, tasty moving parts: succulent chicken, feisty pepper, hearty beans, the slight heat and flavor bounty of chipotle crema, fresh lime (and cilantro lime salt!), and delicious rice. With so much going on, it's amazing it gets distilled into one perfect meal. But amazement is our middle name. (Not Shirley like it says on the old birth certificate.)", "Do you want a restaurant-quality dinner? Don't we all these days. Do you want it in fifteen minutes or less? Look no further than this stunner, with tender pork bathed in a creamy mushroom sauce and garlicky green beans on the side. Quality can come quick, and the best flavors can take no time at all.", "One thing we've learned over the years of providing you with delicious dinners that are easy to make at home: having a meal with both ranch and BBQ sauce is a guaranteed hit. We have the facts, figures, and Excel sheets to prove it. But we've never tried to combine both with the awesome combination of “steak” and “tacos.” These four together might just break our computers, but it'll be worth it to provide you with the flavors you crave. Tip: Easiest way to remove jalapeño stems and seeds: remove ends, then hold upright. Carefully slice the pepper into four pieces, leaving stem and seed to discard."
        };

